cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is about deep learning and specifically focuses on reducing the number of arithmetic operations required for matrix multiplication in deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) since these fields heavily rely on deep learning. The paper also involves optimization and algorithm design, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of sum-product networks (SPNs) could also relate to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
